char* ClientConnect ( int  clientNum,
qboolean  firstTime,
qboolean  isBot 
)

Called when a player begins connecting to the server. Called again for every map change or tournement restart.

The session information will be valid after exit.

Return NULL if the client should be allowed, otherwise return a string with the reason for denial.

Otherwise, the client will be sent the current gamestate and will eventually get to ClientBegin.

Parameters
[in]clientNum
[in]firstTimewill be qtrue the very first time a client connects to the server machine, but qfalse on map changes and tournement restarts.
[in]isBot
Returns
NULL if the client should be allowed, otherwise return a string with the reason for denial.

void G_Damage ( gentity_t *  targ,
gentity_t *  inflictor,
gentity_t *  attacker,
vec3_t  dir,
vec3_t  point,
int  damage,
int  dflags,
meansOfDeath_t  mod 
)

G_Damage.

Parameters
[in,out]targentity that is being damaged
[in,out]inflictorentity that is causing the damage
[in,out]attackerentity that caused the inflictor to damage targ example: targ=monster, inflictor=rocket, attacker=player
[in]dirdirection of the attack for knockback
[in]pointpoint at which the damage is being inflicted, used for headshots
[in]damageamount of damage being inflicted
[in]dflagsthese flags are used to control how T_Damage works DAMAGE_RADIUS damage was indirect (from a nearby explosion) DAMAGE_NO_ARMOR armor does not protect from this damage DAMAGE_NO_KNOCKBACK do not affect velocity, just view angles DAMAGE_NO_PROTECTION kills godmode, armor, everything
[in]mod
Note
inflictor, attacker, dir, and point can be NULL for environmental effects
This parameter was previously present : knockback force to be applied against targ as a result of the damage

: also when damage is 0 ?

void G_EntitySound ( gentity_t *  ent,
const char *  soundId,
int  volume 
)

Plays a sound (wav file or sound script) on this entity.

Parameters
[in]ententity to play the sound on
[in]soundIdsound file name or sound script ID
[in]volumesound volume, only applies to sound file name call
Note
Unused. Keep this.
Calling G_AddEvent(..., EV_GENERAL_SOUND, ...) has the danger of the event never getting through to the client because the entity might not be visible (unless it has the SVF_BROADCAST flag), so if you want to make sure the sound is heard, call this function instead.

void G_PredictPmove ( gentity_t *  ent,
float  frametime 
)

Make use of the 'Pmove' functions to figure out where a player would have moved in the short amount of time indicated by frametime.

After the Pmove is complete, copy the values to the player's entity state, but then copy the original player state values back to the player state so that the player's movements aren't effected in any way.

The only Pmove functions used are PM_StepSlideMove() and PM_GroundTrace() since these are all that is needed for this short period of time. This means that a lot of movement types cannot be predicted and no prediction should be done for them See G_SkipCorrectionSafe()

Parameters
[in,out]ent
[in]frametime

Definition at line 960 of file g_antilag.c.

Referenced by ClientEndFrame().

gentity_t* G_Spawn ( void  )

Either finds a free entity, or allocates a new one.

The slots from 0 to MAX_CLIENTS-1 are always reserved for clients, and will never be used by anything else.

Try to avoid reusing an entity that was recently freed, because it can cause the client to think the entity morphed into something else instead of being removed and recreated, which can cause interpolated angles and bad trails.

Returns
Todo:
: inspect -> add '&& level.startTime != 0' for warmup?
